bxScript – Complete Functional Specification
(All Functions Rayfield Provides, Rewritten as Implementation Requirements)

⸻

CORE LIBRARY STRUCTURE
	1.	Create a Global Library Table

Implement a global table named:

bxScript

This table must contain:
	•	Window creation functions
	•	Notification functions
	•	Destruction logic
	•	Visibility control
	•	Internal flag storage
	•	Theme handling
	•	Configuration saving system

⸻

WINDOW MANAGEMENT FUNCTIONS
	2.	Implement bxScript:CreateWindow(settings)

This function must:
	•	Create the main UI container
	•	Store window metadata (title, subtitle, loading text)
	•	Apply selected theme
	•	Initialize configuration system (if enabled)
	•	Initialize key system (if enabled)
	•	Initialize Discord prompt (if enabled)
	•	Bind toggle key for visibility

Required Settings Support:
	•	Name
	•	LoadingTitle
	•	LoadingSubtitle
	•	ConfigurationSaving:
	•	Enabled
	•	FolderName
	•	FileName
	•	KeySystem
	•	KeySettings
	•	Discord
	•	ToggleUIKeybind

Return: Window object

⸻

	3.	Implement Window:CreateTab(name, icon)

This function must:
	•	Create a tab container
	•	Add navigation button
	•	Support icon rendering (Lucide icon name string)
	•	Register tab inside window tab manager

Return: Tab object

⸻

	4.	Implement Tab:CreateSection(name)

This function must:
	•	Create a section container
	•	Allow grouping of elements
	•	Support title display

Return: Section object

⸻

	5.	Implement Tab:CreateDivider()

This function must:
	•	Insert a visual separator element
	•	Not return interactive value

⸻

INTERACTIVE ELEMENT FUNCTIONS

Each of the following must:
	•	Accept configuration table
	•	Register a unique Flag (if provided)
	•	Store value in internal state system
	•	Connect callback
	•	Support configuration saving

⸻

	6.	Implement Tab:CreateButton(config)

Required Fields:
	•	Name
	•	Callback

Behavior:
	•	Trigger callback when clicked
	•	Do not store persistent state

Return: Button object

⸻

	7.	Implement Tab:CreateToggle(config)

Required Fields:
	•	Name
	•	CurrentValue
	•	Flag
	•	Callback

Behavior:
	•	Store boolean value
	•	Trigger callback on state change
	•	Save/load value if config saving enabled

Return: Toggle object
Must allow programmatic Set(value)

⸻

	8.	Implement Tab:CreateSlider(config)

Required Fields:
	•	Name
	•	Range (min, max)
	•	Increment
	•	CurrentValue
	•	Flag
	•	Callback

Behavior:
	•	Clamp values within range
	•	Snap to increment
	•	Save/load state
	•	Fire callback when changed

Return: Slider object
Must allow programmatic Set(value)

⸻

	9.	Implement Tab:CreateDropdown(config)

Required Fields:
	•	Name
	•	Options (table)
	•	CurrentOption
	•	MultipleOptions (boolean)
	•	Flag
	•	Callback

Behavior:
	•	Allow single or multi-select
	•	Return selected value(s)
	•	Save/load state
	•	Support refreshing options dynamically

Return: Dropdown object
Must include:
	•	Set(options)
	•	Refresh(newOptions)

⸻

	10.	Implement Tab:CreateInput(config)

Required Fields:
	•	Name
	•	PlaceholderText
	•	RemoveTextAfterFocusLost
	•	Flag
	•	Callback

Behavior:
	•	Capture text input
	•	Return string
	•	Save/load state

Return: Input object
Must allow Set(text)

⸻

	11.	Implement Tab:CreateKeybind(config)

Required Fields:
	•	Name
	•	CurrentKeybind
	•	HoldToInteract
	•	Flag
	•	Callback

Behavior:
	•	Detect key press
	•	If HoldToInteract true, fire while held
	•	Save/load assigned key

Return: Keybind object
Must allow Set(key)

⸻

	12.	Implement Tab:CreateColorPicker(config)

Required Fields:
	•	Name
	•	Color (Color3)
	•	Flag
	•	Callback

Behavior:
	•	Return RGB Color3
	•	Save/load color
	•	Fire callback on change

Return: ColorPicker object
Must allow Set(color)

⸻

	13.	Implement Tab:CreateParagraph(config)

Required Fields:
	•	Title
	•	Content

Behavior:
	•	Display static text
	•	Non-interactive

Return: Paragraph object

⸻

GLOBAL UTILITY FUNCTIONS
	14.	Implement bxScript:Notify(config)

Required Fields:
	•	Title
	•	Content
	•	Duration
	•	Icon (optional)

Behavior:
	•	Create temporary popup
	•	Auto-destroy after duration

⸻

	15.	Implement bxScript:Destroy()

Behavior:
	•	Remove entire UI
	•	Disconnect all events
	•	Clear internal state

⸻

	16.	Implement bxScript:SetVisibility(state)

Behavior:
	•	Show or hide main UI container

⸻

	17.	Implement bxScript:IsVisible()

Behavior:
	•	Return true or false

⸻

CONFIGURATION SYSTEM
	18.	Implement Internal Flag System

Requirements:
	•	Store all flagged element values in table
	•	Map Flag string → value
	•	Allow retrieval via internal storage

⸻

	19.	Implement Automatic Saving

If ConfigurationSaving.Enabled:
	•	Create folder (FolderName)
	•	Create file (FileName)
	•	Serialize flag table
	•	Save on value change
	•	Load on UI initialization
	•	Apply loaded values to elements

⸻

KEY SYSTEM
	20.	Implement Key Authentication Layer

If KeySystem = true:
	•	Block window loading until key validated
	•	Display key entry UI
	•	Compare input against KeySettings.Key table
	•	Support SaveKey option
	•	Save key locally if enabled

⸻

DISCORD INTEGRATION
	21.	Implement Discord Prompt

If Discord.Enabled:
	•	Show prompt UI
	•	Use Invite code
	•	Optionally remember join state

⸻

THEME SYSTEM
	22.	Implement Theme Manager

Requirements:
	•	Centralized color palette table
	•	Background colors
	•	Accent colors
	•	Text colors
	•	Hover colors
	•	Element state colors

Allow:
	•	Default theme
	•	Light theme
	•	Custom themes (optional)

All elements must dynamically reference theme values.

⸻

ICON SUPPORT
	23.	Implement Icon Rendering

Requirements:
	•	Accept Lucide icon name string
	•	Render vector icon or mapped asset
	•	Use in tabs and possibly buttons

⸻

DYNAMIC ELEMENT CONTROL
	24.	Each Interactive Element Must Support:

	•	Programmatic Set(value)
	•	Optional Get()
	•	Value update without UI rebuild
	•	Trigger callback on programmatic change (if desired)

⸻

OPTIONAL ADVANCED FEATURES (If Matching Rayfield Gen2)
	25.	Implement:

	•	Resizable window
	•	Tooltips or element descriptions
	•	UI search system
	•	Enhanced layout engine
	•	Developer analytics hook
	•	Monetization hook system

⸻

COMPLETE FUNCTION LIST SUMMARY

bxScript must contain:

Core:
	•	CreateWindow
	•	Notify
	•	Destroy
	•	SetVisibility
	•	IsVisible

Window:
	•	CreateTab

Tab:
	•	CreateSection
	•	CreateDivider
	•	CreateButton
	•	CreateToggle
	•	CreateSlider
	•	CreateDropdown
	•	CreateInput
	•	CreateKeybind
	•	CreateColorPicker
	•	CreateParagraph

Internal Systems:
	•	Flag storage
	•	Config saving/loading
	•	Key authentication
	•	Theme management
	•	Icon support
